articles.description: After winning the College Football Playoff National Championship on Monday, Georgia QB Stetson Bennett took his talents to a local Raising Cane's drive-thru to serve meals to customers.
articles.headline: Georgia Bulldogs QB Stetson Bennett surprises customers at Raising Cane's Chicken restaurant

images.name: UGA's Bennett says 'you work for things like this'
images.caption: QB Stetson Bennett credits Georgia's defense for keeping them in the national championship after offensive mistakes and explains why he "bet" on himself.

images.name: Slade Bolden soars over a defender for an Alabama score
images.caption: Bryce Young dumps one off to Slade Bolden, who takes flight for another Alabama touchdown.

articles.description: Alabama wide receivers Slade Bolden and John Metchie III will enter the NFL draft, while linebacker Henry To'o To'o, defensive lineman DJ Dale and safety Jordan Battle are returning to the team for their senior seasons.
articles.headline: Alabama Crimson Tide receivers Slade Bolden, John Metchie III to enter NFL draft; three defensive starters to return

articles.description: Georgia will be without both of its leading rushers when it tries to defend its national championship in 2022 as junior Zamir White announced Friday he's entering the NFL draft. Senior James Cook announced earlier this week that he is also leaving.
articles.headline: Georgia Bulldogs RB Zamir White joins backfield mate James Cook in declaring for NFL draft

images.name: Caleb Williams [608x342]
images.caption: Freshman Caleb Williams came off the bench to help lead Oklahoma to a thrilling comeback victory over Texas.

images.name: Kedon Slovis [608x342]
images.caption: Kedon Slovis announced he will transfer from USC to Pitt.

images.name: Lyn-j Dixon [608x342]
images.caption: Lyn-J Dixon had 104 carries for 635 yards and six touchdowns with Clemson in 2019, but has totaled only 52 carries for 238 yards in two years since.

images.name: Kai-Leon Herbert [608x342]
images.caption: Senior Kai-Leon Herbert was the No. 99 prospect in the 2017 class. He opted out of the 2020 season and has mainly been a reserve for Miami.

images.name: Marcus Banks [608x342]
images.caption: Former ESPN 300 cornerback Marcus Banks played in 23 total games with Alabama before entering the transfer portal.

images.name: Max Johnson [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: Max Johnson remains in the transfer portal.

images.name: Jadon Haselwood [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: Former Oklahoma wide receiver Jadon Haselwood can play a role in replacing Treylon Burks at Arkansas.

images.name: Quinn Ewers [608x342] - Copy
images.caption: Quinn Ewers will transfer from Ohio State to Texas, he posted on social media.

images.name: Oklahoma vs. Texas (Casey Thompson #11 of the Texas Longhorns looks to pass) [608x342] - Copy (2)
images.caption: Casey Thompson has entered the transfer portal.

images.name: Is Caleb Williams leaving OU?
images.caption: Rod Gilmore and Desmond Howard discuss QB Caleb Williams' decision to enter the transfer portal.

articles.description: More college football players are entering the transfer portal each year. As the season winds down, we will analyze top players as they enter the portal and make new commitments.
articles.headline: College football transfer portal tracker: Top players, predictions, analysis, more

images.name: Travis Dye opens Oregon's scoring with 20-yard rushing TD
images.caption: Oregon's Travis Dye takes the run up the middle for a 20-yard Ducks touchdown.

articles.description: Oregon starting running back Travis Dye has entered the transfer portal after leading the Ducks with 1,271 rushing yards last season.
articles.headline: Oregon RB Travis Dye enters transfer portal after 1,200-yard season

images.name: What's next for the path to CFP expansion?
images.caption: Greg McElroy and Heather Dinich discuss how the committee can eventually come to an agreement and approve a deal for CFP expansion.

articles.description: ACC commissioner Jim Phillips says the conference is against CFP expansion right now because of the uncertain landscape of college football as a whole.
articles.headline: ACC commissioner Jim Phillips says CFP expansion should wait until changes to sport have been evaluated
